NKÚ-Chef: Control of the black system failed due to fault of the policy
The Czech Republic has good control and appropriate laws relating to public contracts, but falls back into their application.
In the interview for Aktuálně.cz the highest control Office says this Miloslav Kala (Nejvyšší Kontrolní urád, NKÚ), Vice President.
"A law is never perfect, but it must be applied correctly and this is not the case in my opinion with us", Kala commented on the current situation.
Apparently also a joint control by Czech and German auditor comes to a similar conclusion.
